text: Hafner Grocery Warehouse is a historic commercial warehouse located at Hannibal, Marion County, Missouri. It was built about 1910, and is a three- story brick structure on a concrete foundation. It features seven bays of segmental-arched windows and a corbelled parapet. and Site map It was added to the National Register of Historic Places in 1986. ==References== Category:Commercial buildings on the National Register of Historic Places in Missouri Category:Commercial buildings completed in 1910 Category:Buildings and structures in Hannibal, Missouri Category:National Register of Historic Places in Marion County, Missouri Category:Grocery store buildings Category:Warehouses on the National Register of Historic Places
